What is an oath?

A formal, solemn promise to fulfill a duty or to uphold a cause

--

What is the Orange Oath?

A formal, solemn promise to expose the immorality of currency inflation and a vow to restore and defend a sound money standard


- A promise to be a ferocious advocate for ending currency inflation
- A vow to shine a light on the darkness of fiat time theft
- An unwavering focus on addressing the core problem: corruption of money
- A vow to advocate for a return to a sound money standard where our currency is backed by real world hard assets


An oath taken by all members of the Canadian Orange Party (civilians, operators, parliamentarians) 

- I vow to be a vocal advocate for a return to sound money
- I vow to vocalize the immorality, unfairness and harms caused by currency inflation
- I stand for truth and act with integrity for the benefit of Canadians
- I vow to be a courageous, loud advocate for ending currency inflation and returning to a sound money standard in Canada


Find based members of parliament who speak truth, educate them about money and inflation, arm them with potent speaking points that serve as daggers to puncture the veil of lies being constantly spewed by fiat parasites




